As a professional athlete, I’ve worked hard to receive the same recognition as my male counterparts.  I’ve benefited from support from strong women in leadership, on my teams and community!  In a world where only 5% of all sports coverage features female athletes, today I am proud to be part of #TeamMilk, and their commitment to featuring 100% women in all of their campaigns. When we all have visibility, opportunity and equity; we all WIN.  For more information on Milk’s efforts check out GonnaNeedMilk.com/26.2  #ad #gonnaneedmilk @gonnaneedmilk 📸 : @amandakayedelgado

With the mission to empower young esports players by creating a healthier competition environment, the House launched the Gucci Gaming Academy together with FACEIT and in collaboration with the World Health Organization. To extend the impact, it presents GG Legends, a mini docuseries showing how some of the most successful players in the world of gaming and esports overcame adversity to achieve greatness.

The latest episode follows me and captures my story as an WNBA player and esports gamer and highlights how I found purpose through gaming by creating space for women and people of color. GG Legends follows my journey from a young girl in Detroit to becoming a co-owner of Team Liquid and Chair of its Diversity & Inclusion Task Force. Watch the full episode on YouTube.  Type in: Title - GG Legends Aerial Powers

March 2023 ✅ it’s not about the destination but the journey!! This march I’ve had the pleasure to..
•Be on the bump for WWE( being in the ring is a childhood dream of mine! I’ve been a fan of WWE since The Rock days! So it was more than an honor to be on the podcast!)
•The Gucci Documentary launched!! ( this one was extremely special to me because I was able to share with the world how AMAZING my father is and what it’s like growing up in my hometown Detroit from my own perspective)
•Jumpman launched its newest campaign (when I was a young girl and even right before college games I would watch videos of MJ!! I still watch videos NOW!! Now look at me signed by the man who built the brand!! Crazy🤯🤯 seeing myself in the campaign literally means more to me than many know so I thought I would share a little insight! Then seeing the movie AIR and how the brand came to be I’m even more 🤯🤯. Mama Jordan is a BADDDD woman to negotiate a deal that would change there families lives FOEVER! MJ is the 🐐 but Mama Deloris is the true 🐐. Go head queen!)
Okay enough let me stop ranting ☺️
🥂 to more life and sharing the journey along the way 🥂

Aerial Powers is a dynamic guard for the Minnesota Lynx known for her strong attacking ability at the rim. Her versatility shines as she's not only a threat inside, but also has a reliable 3-point shot. With her quickness and agility, she's a force to be reckoned with on the court. A Michigan State University alumni, Powers brings a well-rounded skill set to the Lynx roster.
